{"lemma":"صَوْبٌ","slug":"صَوْبٌ","root":"ص.#.ب","root_slug":"ص-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25117"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to aim, point, or direct (something, such as a ranged weapon, like an arrow)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to amend (something deemed to be a mistake or an error), to correct, to rectify, to right, to remedy; to straighten","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to inform (someone) that he or she is correct; to deem (someone or something, such as an opinion) acceptable, correct, or conforming; to agree with, to concur with; to consent to","tags":["dated","often","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to inform (someone) that he or she is correct; to deem (someone or something, such as an opinion) acceptable, correct, or conforming; to approve; to sanction; to validate; to confirm; to verify","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, direction"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"in the direction of, towards","examples":[{"text":"أطلقت قوات الاحتلال النيران بكثافة صوب الشاب ما أدى إلى إصابته بجروح بالغة الخطورة.","english":"The occupation forces launched the fire densely towards the young man which lead to serious wounds being inflicted on him."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤaw.wa.ba/","/sˤawb/","/sˤaw.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25117","headword_ar":"صَوْبٌ","root":"Swb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. used as a subst. (Msb) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ibN","text_ar":"صَيِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is originally ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayowibN","text_ar":"صَيْوِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEilN","text_ar":"فَيْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~awobu","text_ar":"الصَّوْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd in ii. 18:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ibN","text_ar":"صَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to clouds ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayomN","text_ar":"غَيْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Sh, O, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Msb) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw SawobK","text_ar":"ذُو صَوْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawobN","text_ar":"صَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ibN","text_ar":"صَيِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~uwbN","text_ar":"صَيُّوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the last of which is written in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayuwbN","text_ar":"صَيُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] all signify the same, (M, K,) as epithets applied to rain, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~uwbN","text_ar":"صَيُّوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is originally of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEuwlN","text_ar":"فَيْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [being altered from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayowuwbN","text_ar":"صَيْوُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] means rain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundantly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O:) [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAy^ibN","text_ar":"صَايِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is applied as an epithet to rain, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawobN","text_ar":"صَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ibN","text_ar":"صَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and] in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiybaAnu AlmaTari","text_ar":"صِيبَانُ المَطَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Abu-l-'Alà,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiybaAn","text_ar":"صِيبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAy^ib","text_ar":"صَايِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiromaAn","text_ar":"حِرْمَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": and if one say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayobaAn","text_ar":"صَيْبَان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has poured forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of rain, notwithstanding the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in it, for similar to this are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rayoHaAn","text_ar":"رَيْحَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~awoH","text_ar":"الرَّوْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayodaAn","text_ar":"عَيْدَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning “ tall ” palm-trees) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuwod","text_ar":"العُوْد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 796.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodN","text_ar":"قَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the saying, to one who is traversing a desert in uncertainty and has declined from the right way,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqimo Sawobaka","text_ar":"اَقِمْ صَوْبَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rectify thy course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN musotaqiymu AlS~awobi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مُسْتَقِيمُ الصَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is pursuing the right course"},{"kind":"text","text":"], said of a person when he is not declining from his way to the right or left. (TA. [See also another ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awobN","text_ar":"اَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point, of tendency"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jihapN","text_ar":"جِهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) of a thing; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHiyapN","text_ar":"نَاحِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means the same; and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adjacent, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; and in this sense"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawobN","text_ar":"صَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the present day]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which generally has the latter of these meanings]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAbN","text_ar":"صَوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["Msb","O","S","M","K","IDrd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}